        "text": "and p. 178: Another point that has always fascinated me concerns the question of what happens when two complex systems get involved with each other, when they are coupled or interact and do not have the ability to duplicate the complexity of the other in their own system, that is, do not have the \"requisite variety\" that would be required to map another system into themselves. "
